<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="abcb-glossentry" ?><abcb-glossentry xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" outputclass="abcb-glossentry"><glossterm id="_30bcffe8-cab8-44e2-9437-44dcb76bee8a">Drainage system</glossterm><glossdef outputclass="glossdef"><p>A system that—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_ad627119-037a-4555-9e11-ea5a0b6515cb">conveys <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9511_0.7.0.xml#_022a6a17-e1b4-412a-b84c-3ea9c214b02c" id="_22e88e28-f9e9-4dad-a28a-03a0fb40ef9b" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">water</xref> by gravity, mechanical means, or evaporation to a point of discharge or evaporative surface; or</li><li id="_5962bc57-704e-4ed4-809d-4768d00f083b">channels <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9511_0.7.0.xml#_022a6a17-e1b4-412a-b84c-3ea9c214b02c" id="_4afefafd-80a2-4023-b5d2-8c16c8bc183e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">water</xref> by pipes, overflows, and overland flow paths to a point of discharge.</li></ol><callout id="_f2ad104c-b17e-4421-abfd-1549df5872bb"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>The definition for ‘drainage system’ is used only for the purposes of Volume One Section F.</p></callout></glossdef></abcb-glossentry>